Law professor Makau Mutua relaxed with politicians including opposition leader Raila Odinga at his Kitui home on Tuesday, following its conversion into a hotel. The ODM leader was invited to the launch of Kitui Villa alongside people including his wife Ida, Wiper leaderÂ Kalonzo Musyoka and Kitui Governor Charity Ngilu. Moses Wetang'ula, who is Bungoma Senator and Ford Kenya leader, was expected to grace to occasion. In a tweet, Raila said: "I appeal to Kenyans in the diaspora to invest in counties." He will open Kitui bus park later in the day.  ODM leader Raila Odinga at law professor Makau Mutua's Kitui Villa following its launch on July 10, 2018. /COURTESY  Law professor Makau Mutua, ODM leader Raila Odinga and Wiper boss Kalonzo Musyoka open the professor's Kitui Villa on July 10, 2018. /COURTESY  Wiper boss Kalonzo Musyoka, law professor Makau Mutua and ODM leader Raila Odinga during the launch of the professor's Kitui Villa, July 10, 2018. /COURTESY  Wiper boss Kalonzo Musyoka, law professor Makau Mutua, ODM leader Raila Odinga, his wife Ida and Kitui Governor Charity Ngilu during the launch of the professor's Kitui Villa, July 10, 2018. /COURTESY  Ida Odinga with other guests during the launch of law professor Makau Mutua's Kitui Villa, July 10, 2018. /COURTESY  ODM leader Raila Odinga with law professor Makau Mutua at his Kitui Villa following its launch on July 10, 2018. /COURTESY  A section of law professor Makau Mutua's Kitui Villa which was launched on July 10, 2018. /COURTESY Click here for the latest political news